## The code book describes all variables and units

## The site where the full description is available is http://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/datasets/Human+Activity+Recognition+Using+Smartphones

## The data for the project is https://d396qusza40orc.cloudfront.net/getdata%2Fprojectfiles%2FUCI%20HAR%20Dataset.zip

# The zip file contains 2 folders namely test and train and 4 tables namely activity_labels.txt, features.txt, features_info.txt, and README.txt
# The test folder contains another folder namely Inertial Signals and 3 tables namely subject_test.txt, X_test.txt, and y_test.txt
# The Inertial Signals folder contains 9 tables namely body_acc__x_test.txt, body_acc__y_test.txt, body_acc__z_test.txt,
#                                                      body_gyro__x_test.txt, body_gyro__y_test.txt, body_gyro__z_test.txt
#                                                      total_acc__x_test.txt, total_acc__y_test.txt, total_acc__z_test.txt
# The train folder contains another folder namely Inertial Signals and 3 tables namely subject_train.txt, X_train.txt, and y_train.txt
# The Inertial Signals folder contains 9 tables namely body_acc__x_train.txt, body_acc__y_train.txt, body_acc__z_train.txt,
#                                                      body_gyro__x_train.txt, body_gyro__y_train.txt, body_gyro__z_train.txt
#                                                      total_acc__x_train.txt, total_acc__y_train.txt, total_acc__z_train.txt

